        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 20 at 8:11PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 811 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 6
miles east of Uptown Charlotte, or near East Charlotte, moving east
at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Uptown Charlotte, South Charlotte, East Charlotte, Matthews, Mint
Hill, Reedy Creek Park, The Plaza, Hidden Valley, Southpark Mall, and
The Arboretum.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
